  <span id="freeText11791121403883713502" style="display:none">This book is a hard one for me to decide how to rate. There were parts of it I really liked and there were parts of it when I thought my eyes would glaze over and never recover. <br>Laurel is given an assignment to write to a dead person. She begins to do so and never turns in the assignment. Once she starts she keeps going with it and changes to several past celebrities and historical figures. She has moved to a new school to help cope with her sister Mae's death. Hoping that a new school will shield her from any one that knew her sister. <br>The teenage angst in this book is way over the top for me. I felt old just reading it. I love YA books and have read some great ones but this one fell so very short for me. <br><a href="http://s926.photobucket.com/user/bookqueenshelby/media/i-feel-old-as-fuck-right-now-20887_zps164b95c8.jpg.html" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">
